codex
Created minimal .NET 8 minimal API with omnichannel domain model and SQL schema.

- Web API entrypoint with sample endpoints for products, orders, returns, and loyalty in `LCP-Vibe-2/src/Program.cs`. Includes in-memory inventory service, tax calculator, and loyalty engine plus Swagger wiring.
- Domain layer defining 30 distinct classes (including PerishableGoods, LuxuryItems, DigitalDownloads, LoyaltyProgram, InventoryAudit, TaxCalculator usage, ReturnAuthorization, etc.) in `LCP-Vibe-2/src/Models/Domain.cs`.
- SQL schema covering products (with perishable/luxury/digital fields), orders, payments, returns, loyalty, fulfillment, logistics, POS, and omnichannel mappings in `LCP-Vibe-2/schema.sql`.
- Project file targeting .NET 8 in `LCP-Vibe-2/src/LcpVibe2.csproj`.

Next steps:
1) From `LCP-Vibe-2/src`, run `dotnet restore` then `dotnet run` to start the API (Swagger available in Development).  
2) Point a database at `schema.sql` and hook up persistence/repositories as needed.  
3) Extend controllers/endpoints to cover full CRUD and authorization.
